    d.
        i.
            Cloud storage is storage on another computer, or on a server, which is accessed via the internet.
        ii.
            Data can be shared with other people more easily, as it simply requires sharing access credentials as the data is stored online anyways
            Data is generally backed up automatically on cloud storage, so there is much less risk of data loss due to physical damage to storage media.
    e?
        Because a general-purpose computer must be able to run arbitrary software and do arbitrary tasks. Time and text messages do not encompass arbitrary software or tasks.
5.
    a?
        The barcode scanning system uses a check digit to check for errors in data on input. This means that the barcode scanning system calculates some value from all the other digits in the barcode, possibly via summing them modulo some number (such as 10), and compares it to the check digit. If this calculated value is not the same as the check digit, then the barcode-scanning system knows that there has been an error. This is because the check digit is calculated in the same way from the same data, so either the initial calculation has gone wrong, or the check-digit has been misread, or one of the other digits has been misread, or the final calculation has gone wrong. This, however, does not account for some errors which may not affect the check digit, such as transposition errors.
    b.
        i?
            Serial simplex data transmission means that the data-line can only transmit data one way, and that bits are sent one at a time.
            The data is sent bit by bit alongside a clock-signal for synchronisation or else at a pre-arranged frequency. Because it is simplex, there is no risk of crosstalk or data collision. The clock-signal or pre-arranged frequency is used and the voltage in the data line at every clock cycle/at the pre-arranged interval is read and converted into either a 1 or a 0. Since the data is numeric, it can be converted into binary and sent as 1s and 0s.
        ii.
            Because there is not much data to be sent, speed is not an issue, so serial data transmission is appropriate.
            Because there is no foreseeable future where the barcode scanner must receive data or transmissions from the stock control system, there is no need for half-duplex or duplex transmission. Simplex is the most simple and low-cost, so it is the most appropriate.
        iii?
            1
                Echo check
            2
                Parity bit
